Women had marched to Governor Okalia's office to call for an end to the Anglophone crisis, according to journalist Mimi Mefo. He then addressing the crowd. "When I have asked you before, 'who are the killers?' You said you don't know," he said. "Who are the killers?" he asked, and the crowd answered in unison "We don't know". He then responded: "The killers are your brothers, the killers are your children, the killers are people living amongst you and you do not want to denounce them."
